headline.main: Eugene O'Neill Dies of Pneumonia; Playwright, 65, Won Nobel Prize; He Also Took Pulitzer Award for Drama Three Times -Ill for Several Years EUGENE O'NEILL, 65, DIES OF PNEUMONIA

snippet: BOSTON, Nov. 27 -- Eugene O'Neill, noted American playwright whose prolific talents had brought to him both Nobel and Pulitzer Prizes, died today of bronchial pneumonia. His age was 65.

byline.original: Special to THE NEW YORK TIMES
